  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">In this letter, Lucretia Mott comments on the new book, Despotism in America, which she has &quot;since read with deep interest.&quot; [Despotism in America is by Richard Hildreth, Boston, 1840.] Lucretia Mott wishes David Lee Child and Lydia Maria Child would settle in Philadelphia. Anna M. Hopper wishes that Mrs. Child would open a school for young children, but Lucretia Mott is more concerned that she should be sent to the World&apos;s Convention. In reference to the division between the New and Old Organizations, Lucretia Mott hopes that J. G. Whittier will have his eyes opened, but he &quot;seems to be blinded.&quot; She describes an incident in Smyrna, Delaware, where D. Neall was tarred and feathered.</subfield>
